{
  "text": "Hussain et al. [CITATION_1] found significantly higher faecal 5-ASA amounts by increasing Asacol from 1.2 to 2.4 g daily but a higher dose of 4.8 g daily did not significantly further increase faecal excretion. Lauritsen et al. [CITATION_2] detected higher faecal 5-ASA concentrations for a higher dose of Olsalazine in patients with UC. In our systematic analysis, as shown in Figure 3a , a higher dose of oral 5-ASA correlates with a higher faecal concentration. This dose-concentration effect was even more evident if only high validity studies were included. However, this effect was less pronounced if faecal 5-ASA is expressed as recovery of ingested dose or total amount (Fig. 3b, c) .",
  "correct_citation": {
